```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int = 3)
    @assert isa(dt, DateTime) "Input must be a DateTime type."
    return dt + Hours(bump)
end
```

This function checks if the input is a DateTime type using the `isa` function. If not, it throws an error with a custom message. If the input is valid, it uses the `Hours` function to add the specified number of hours to the DateTime object and returns the result.
